<IMG SRC="http://www.plattsflello.com/ryn.gif" BORDER=0></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utheodwynriddermark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TheodwynRiddermark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 210<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/10/02 1:39:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2888.topic&index=59>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NBG is BS!</span><hr size=1> I'm not getting into the statistical argument of chances of winning what roll where, etc.<br>
<br>
The thing that surprises me the most is the tennet of fairness.<br>
<br>
I don't know any of your personal backgrounds, how old you are, your socio-economic status, or what have you; but I'd like to introduce one thing for thought here.<br>
<br>
&quot;Fair&quot; and &quot;Right&quot; are very very often not the same thing.  Very very often, the &quot;right&quot; thing to do is not necessarily the &quot;fair&quot; thing.<br>
<br>
&quot;Right&quot; is an idea influenced by values, morals, etc, etc, etc.<br>
<br>
&quot;Fair&quot; is likewise subjective.<br>
<br>
So before you spout about how FFA is fair, think about whether or not it's right.<br>
<br>
The entire argument of getting screwed over 99 times being justified by the 1 time it proves worthwhile is entirely dependent on your view of what is the worthwhile price of doing what is right in your own eyes and in your own view.<br>
<br>
For those of you who argue that FFA is more &quot;fair&quot;, your idea of fairness is based on a compromise that you wish to make regarding statistical chances related to monetary/gear gain.  That everyone gets a chance to profit of the spoil, and will therefore purchase what they choose when they choose for what they choose later on down the line.<br>
<br>
For those of you who argue that NBG is more &quot;right&quot;, your idea of righteousness is based on a compromise with yourself that giving up your shot at a roll will come back to you later on down the line based on a faith that if you give people what they need when they need it (whether they lie to you or not), your honesty and faith will be rewarded in getting what you need when you need it.<br>
<br>
I don't sell.  So FFA means entirely crap to me.  I won't profit off it whether I win an item or not.  The best I'd do with a won item is twink a guildie with it.  And I don't like twinking people.  I don't happen to believe in buying friends, or giving another player the quick way out of having to learn, camp, and put in effort like everyone else of like mindset to myself.  So again, FFA means entirely crap to me.<br>
<br>
I believe in tradeskills, if I'm going to give someone a leg up, high tradeskill crafted items is more than adequate for giving someone a headstart, without giving or selling rare and valuable items obtained later in the game; items which were dropped by by the effort of someone(s) else.<br>
<br>
Notice we're all kind of opinionated?  Well yeah.  So here's my conclusion.<br>
<br>
You like FFA, more power to you.  Just do me a favor and don't try ramming down my throat how it's more &quot;fair&quot; or what have you.  As a person (therefore as a player), I see &quot;fairness&quot; espoused as the holy solution of the week (can we say people at my door with a copy of &quot;The Watchtower&quot;).<br>
<br>
For myself and those other NBG believers, I realize my idea of &quot;nobility&quot; and &quot;karma&quot; is my own, and I don't seek to ram it down anyone's throat.  It's my preference, it's my belief, I stick by it.  If you are attracted to the term &quot;nobility&quot;, which is an ideal which by definition must persist even in the face of tons of unfairness and bullshit, then you might share my view.  If not, then obviously what I believe is not for you.<br>
<br>
Cheers,<br>
Theo<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucoroq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Coroq</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 228<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/10/02 2:05:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2888.topic&index=60>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> You people make this seem far more complex than it is</span><hr size=1> Nice debate. Here's where I come down.<br>
