GBN, or roll on everything just feels like loot whoring to me. Sorry, I just don't like it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usalenie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salenie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 154<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/10/02 2:08:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2888.topic&index=61>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NBG is BS!</span><hr size=1> Personally, I like sneaky NBG.  If I'm in a FFA group and I win something someone else would obviously use, I give it to them.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Otherwise it goes to guild or friends.  I detest E(Bay)Commons and avoid it as much as possible.<br>
<br>
